parameters.name: UT
parameters.description: Universal Time given in PDS format: yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss.sss.

parameters.name: X_VSO
parameters.description:
The X-component of the PVO spacecraft position in Venus Solar Orbital   
      Coordinates (VSO). The X component of the VSO coordinate system is taken
      to be positive in the direction of the Sun measured along the Venus-Sun 
      line. The units are given in Venus Radii where Rv = 6050 km.

parameters.name: Y_VSO
parameters.description:
The Y-component of the PVO spacecraft position in Venus Solar Orbital   
      Coordinates (VSO).The Y component of the VSO coordinate system is taken 
      to be positive in the direction opposing orbital motion (dusk) and lying
      in the orbital plane of Venus. The units are given in Venus Radii where 
      Rv = 6050 km.

parameters.name: Z_VSO
parameters.description:
The Z-component of the PVO spacecraft position in Venus Solar Orbital   
      Coordinates (VSO). The Z component of the VSO coordinate system is taken
      to be parallel to the pole of the Venus orbital plane and positive in   
      the northward direction (upward normal).  The units are given in Venus  
      Radii where Rv = 6050 km.

parameters.name: ALT
parameters.description:
Spacecraft Altitude above the Venus surface. This value is computed by  
      subtracting 6050 km from the centered Venus-to-PVO range given in the   
      SEDR.

parameters.name: SZA
parameters.description:
Solar Zenith Angle. This is the three body angle Sun-Venus-PVO taken    
      from the SEDR.

parameters.name: PLONG
parameters.description: Venus centered longitude of the PVO spacecraft.

parameters.name: PLAT
parameters.description: Venus centered latitude of the PVO spacecraft.

parameters.name: SPX_VSO
parameters.description: The VSO X-component of the spacecraft spin axis (ISCC_Z).

parameters.name: SPY_VSO
parameters.description: The VSO Y-component of the spacecraft spin axis (ISCC_Z).

parameters.name: SPZ_VSO
parameters.description: The VSO Z-component of the spacecraft spin axis (ISCC_Z).

parameters.name: CLAT
parameters.description: Heliocentric Celestial Latitude of the PVO spacecraft.

parameters.name: CLONG
parameters.description: Heliocentric Celestial Longitude of the PVO spacecraft.

parameters.name: ELONG
parameters.description: Heliocentric Celestial Longitude of the Earth.
